HEADWORD: Trochee
<hw>Tro"chee</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trochaeus</ets>, Gr. <?/ (sc.<?/), from <?/ running, from <?/ to
run. Cf. <er>Troche</er>, <er>Truck</er> a wheel.]</ety>
<fld>(Pros.)</fld> <def>A foot of two syllables, the first long and the
second short, as in the Latin word <xex>ante</xex>, or the first
accented and the second unaccented, as in the English word
<xex>motion</xex>; a choreus.</def>⟦br⟧
